reviewText:
A highly underrated game from 2012, that is now being refurbished for 2014 in the Definitive Edition {}^__^}

If you don't own it already, grab a this 'version' of the game cheap via third-party (with no DLC's) then activate it on Steam. Once activated, check the Definitive Edition store page, which will now show you a 50% discount, which not only includes a totally revamped game (which was already great), but all the DLC's from the original version and then some for the 2014 release \[]^__^]/

***3/3*** - My original thoughts in 2012 still stand and I'm looking forward to completing it fully in the 2014 update []^....^]

